OL,3,CShould authorities have told us more
OL,4,Cabout the Southport killer?
OL,6,FIf a publication carries a
OL,7,F"substantial risk of serious
OL,8,Fprejudice" ` in other words, could
OL,9,Fseriously impede the ability of a jury
OL,10,Fto reach a fair verdict ` it could
OL,11,Flead to the collapse of a trial.
OL,13,FOn paper, that rule applies from the
OL,14,Fmoment a suspect is arrested. However,
OL,15,Fin practice, the risk is seen as much
OL,16,Fgreater once they have been charged.
